The paper discusses data auditing in cloud servers, which is a security issue, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with data storage and retrieval, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DB (Databases). The use of proofs of retrievability (POR) is a technique used in distributed systems, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of POR in cloud systems, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
